title: Alpha-particle production in 6He + 120Sn collisions

x4freetext: Alpha-particle production in 6He + 120Sn collisions

Comision Nacional de Energia Atomica, Buenos Aires, Argentina

x4codes.hlp: Univ.de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, Brazil

x4freetext: 8UD Sao Paulo Pelletron Laboratory
using the  Radioactive Ion Beams in Brasil (RIBRAS)
system.
The 7Li primary beam of energies in the range
E(lab)=24-26 MeV and intensities of about 300 nA e
focused on a 12 mu-m 9Be foil in which the 6He  beam
was was produced via the 9Be(7Li,6He)10B reaction.
The 6He beam was collected and focused by the first
solenoid on the secondary target position.

flag.help: Reference to related data compiled in another entry

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.81, p.044605 (2010)

x4freetext: Detailed description of the RIBRAS system and
cross section normalization.
A 3.8 mg/cm2 120Sn (98.29%) foil was used as
secondary target. An array consisting of four  delta-
E(20mu-m)-E(1000mu-m) silicon telescopes  allows the
detection and identification of the charged
particles emerging from the reaction.
The gold
target was used for normalization purposes because the
6He + 197Au scattering is pure Rutherford at the
energies and angular range of the experiment.
An array consisting of four
deltaE(20mu-m)-E(1000mu-m) silicon  telescopes allows
the detection and identification of the charged
particles emerging from the reaction.
Approved by authors 2011-07-14.
Data digitized from Fig. 2 in the reference.
LV, VS.
Because of the low statistics the spectra at a few
angles around 50-75 degrees where the peak is more
visible were summed up and  the double differential
cross sections were calculated.
